  8. Reviews

    · 44
    • Lake Country Inn
      Extremely wonderful bedrooms, very inviting, clean and unique. The Tower Suite specifically was amazing and the bed was the single comfiest bed I have experienced. The fireplace and heat from the vents were silent, very quiet and peaceful. The large windows are nice, and there is a mounted smart TV on the wall with all the hookups you need to Chrome cast or hookup a laptop to stream your favorite shows. There is a mini fridge / freezer in the room, and the kitchen downstairs has a microwave and plates for leftovers. Everything about the Lake Country Inn is well cared for and the interior design is very thoughtful. It truly is like being in a home away from home. Across the street is an Italian restaurant that provided the most authentic Italian dinner experience I have had since I returned from Italy. I highly recommend anyone that wants a peaceful getaway and a comfortable, quality experience in a homely atmosphere. The owner and attendant are very sweet and nice, and everything is within walking distance, including downtown, the nearest beach and Oink's ice cream. We definitely plan on returning!
